**Description:** **: This code is a Python module that defines a class `APIAnalyzer`, which inherits from `BaseTool`. Its primary purpose is to analyze API services, with a focus on accessibility features. It categorizes APIs, checks for payment requirements, identifies accessibility features like text-to-speech or alt text, and generates structured reports. The class includes methods for initialization, categorization, feature analysis, key analysis, report generation, and execution, making it a tool for processing and evaluating API data.

```python
from typing import Dict, List, Optional, Any
from dataclasses import dataclass
from ...base import BaseTool
import json
import re

@dataclass
class APIService:
    """Represents an API service with accessibility information."""
    name: str
    key: str
    category: str
    requires_payment: bool
    accessibility_features: List[str]
    documentation_url: Optional[str] = None

class APIAnalyzer(BaseTool):
    """Tool for analyzing API services with focus on accessibility features."""
    
    def __init__(self):
        super().__init__()
        self.services: Dict[str, APIService] = {}
        self.free_apis = {
            "semantic_scholar": "https://api.semanticscholar.org/",
            "arxiv": "https://arxiv.org/help/api/",
            "unpaywall": "https://unpaywall.org/products/api",
            "open_library": "https://openlibrary.org/developers/api",
            "gutendex": "https://gutendex.com/",
            "courtlistener": "https://www.courtlistener.com/api/",
      
